{
  "texts": [
    "Later on, a cross-check per question across models was performed to assure an equal treatment of each model, since human evaluation comes with the risk of subjectivity.",
    "In initial tests, BloomZ was the best model in the 7B parameter range with 35.5% accuracy.",
    "It outperforms Alpaca 7B (chavinlo, 33.6%) in our experiments, but only by a small margin (see table 1).",
    "Alpaca is based on LLaMA 7B and chavinlos model is not improving the already good base performance of LLaMA a lot (32.7%).",
    "However, it was unclear whether the replication of Stanford's Alpaca that is hosted publicly on Huggingface (chavinlo/alpaca-native) is really performing as good as the original."
  ]
}